<item>
            <title>[HBASE-3696] No durability when running with LocalFileSystem</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-3696</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;LocalFileSystem in Hadoop doesn&apos;t currently implement sync(), so when we&apos;re running in that case, we don&apos;t have any durability. This isn&apos;t a huge deal since it isn&apos;t a realistic deployment scenario, but it&apos;s probably worth documenting. It caused some confusion for a user when a table disappeared after killing a standalone instance that was hosting its data in the local FS.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
